  <div class="note-tag">Verdict</div>
  <div class="verdict-box">
    <p>The RX 6700 XT was AMD's mid-range effort in RDNA 2, and it aged pretty well. The Navi 22 die on 7nm, 2560 stream processors, and 96MB of Infinity Cache make it a genuinely solid 1080p and 1440p GPU. The 12GB GDDR6 on a 192-bit bus is compensated heavily by that Infinity Cache. At $479 MSRP it was competitive with the RTX 3070, and in rasterization it kept up reasonably well. In 2024-2025 it can still handle 1440p gaming at medium-high settings in most titles. A good used card pickup today if the price is right.</p>
  </div>
 
